
[1]superintend

   SUPERINTEND', v.t. [super and intend.] To have or exercise the charge
   and oversight of; to oversee with the power of direction; to take care
   of with authority; as, an officer superintends the building of a ship
   or the construction of a fort. God exercises a superintending care over
   all his creatures.
